# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Type:
#   feat     - New feature
#   fix      - Bug fix
#   refactor - Code refactoring (no functional change)
#   docs     - Documentation only
#   style    - Code style (formatting, missing semicolons, etc)
#   test     - Adding or updating tests
#   chore    - Build process, dependencies, CI changes
#   perf     - Performance improvement
#
# Scope (optional):
#   project  - Project management module
#   version  - Version management module
#   spec     - Spec editing module
#   scaffold - Scaffold generation module
#   review   - Review flow module
#   execution- Code execution module
#   runtime  - Runtime management module
#   dashboard- Dashboard module
#   ipc      - IPC layer
#   ui       - UI components
#   store    - State management
#   infra    - Infrastructure (adapters, repos)
#   config   - Configuration
#
# Subject:
#   - Use imperative mood: "add" not "added" or "adds"
#   - Don't capitalize first letter
#   - No period at the end
#   - Max 50 characters
#
# Body (optional):
#   - Explain what and why, not how
#   - Wrap at 72 characters
#
# Footer (optional):
#   - Reference issues: "Closes #123" or "Refs #456"
#   - Breaking changes: "BREAKING CHANGE: description"
#
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Examples:
#
#   feat(project): add create project use case
#
#   fix(execution): handle task failure correctly
#
#   Execution was not properly handling task failures.
#   Now it emits taskFailed event and waits for user decision.
#
#   Closes #42
#
#   refactor(store): simplify realtime store subscription
#
#   chore: update dependencies
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
